  "text": "Topical community detection. Relevant literature includes a wide range of works for topic labelling (for a full survey on the area, see [CITATION_1] ). Our work is part of those works that make use of external datasources to label topics. In [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , topics are extracted from Wikipedia's structured knowledge, also verifying the topics against a search engine [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Moving away from Wikipedia and built-in knowledge bases into Linked Data, [CITATION_7] proposes to use DBpedia categories as labels for topics. This work is certainly the most similar to our research, but with a significant difference: [CITATION_8] relies on the use of SPARQL queries to retrieve the DBpedia categories. This introduces some (human) a priori knowledge, and limits the benefits of the Linked Data interconnected knowledge, intended as a more serendipitous knowledge discovery process.",
